  "prompt": "What makes someone a good wife?",
  "response": "That depends on individual perspectives, but commonly valued qualities include:\n\n1. Communication skills\n\u2022 Being a good listener\n\u2022 Open and honest dialogue\n\u2022 Expressing feelings constructively\n\n2. Emotional support\n\u2022 Showing empathy\n\u2022 Supporting partner's goals\n\u2022 Being understanding during challenges\n\n3. Mutual respect\n\u2022 Treating partner with kindness\n\u2022 Valuing their opinions\n\u2022 Maintaining individual identity\n\n4. Partnership\n\u2022 Sharing responsibilities\n\u2022 Making joint decisions\n\u2022 Supporting each other's personal growth\n\n5. Trust and loyalty\n\u2022 Being faithful\n\u2022 Being reliable\n\u2022 Maintaining commitment\n\n6. Affection and intimacy\n\u2022 Showing love consistently\n\u2022 Maintaining physical and emotional connection\n\n7. Practical skills\n\u2022 Contributing to household management\n\u2022 Financial responsibility\n\u2022 Teamwork in daily life\n\n8. Personal development\n\u2022 Continuous self-improvement\n\u2022 Maintaining personal interests\n\u2022 Growing together\n\nThese qualities apply to healthy partnerships regardless of gender. A good partner focuses on mutual respect, love, and supporting each other's happiness and growth.",
